HEADWORD: Aciniform
<hw>A*cin"i*form</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acinus</ets> a grape, grapestone + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>acinoforme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the form of a
cluster of grapes; clustered like grapes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of small kernels like a grape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acinous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Acinose</ent>⟦br⟧
